National Cooperation Urged 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 3 (KCNA) -- National cooperation today stands out with great urgency for a progress in the movement for the independent reunification of the country, says Rodong Sinmun in a signed article today.
 It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The United States is throwing grave barriers in the way of Korea's reunification by persistently resorting to moves to stifle the DPRK under the pretext of the nuclear issue with it and is now bringing dark clouds of a nuclear war over the Korean nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 National cooperation is the major way for building a structure of confrontation between the Korean nation and the U.S. by practical actions. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The fanatic nuclear racket of the U.S. imperialists against the DPRK places at risk the destiny of all the Koreans, not that of the people in the north alone. Nationwide fighting ranks must be formed against the U.S. bent on harassing peace, hindering Korea's reunification and inflicting a nuclear holocaust upon the Korean nation. In other words, the structure of confrontation between the Korean nation and the U.S. should be built in the struggle to achieve peace and independent reunification of the nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 National cooperation means solving all the problems of the nation related to its destiny and prospect by its concerted efforts, not relying upon outsiders, and keeping pace in this. Through active cooperation all the Koreans at home and abroad can form a strong common front of the nation against the U.S. which is seeking to draw water to its mill, in poking its nose into the internal affairs of the Korean nation and laying stubborn roadblocks in its way. Thus the structure of confrontation between the Korean nation and the U.S. must be built by practical actions. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 National cooperation is the main guarantee for the Korean nation to win in the confrontation with the U.S. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The driving force in the struggle against the U.S. and war is the Korean nation and its unity is the guarantee for victory. The Korean nation can drive away aggressive outsiders and achieve peace and independent reunification of the nation only when they wage a relentless struggle against the U.S. and war, closely united under the banner of the June 15 North-South Joint Declaration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 National cooperation is to reject outsiders and seek reconciliation and unity of all the Koreans. It makes it possible for the Koreans to pool their strength and wisdom and frustrate any moves to cooperate with the U.S. and maneuvers of outsiders against reunification and peace with the mighty force of great national unity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 National cooperation is immediately great unity and the guarantee for a decisive victory in the struggle against the U.S. and war. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All the Koreans should build a structure of confrontation between the entire Korean nation and the U.S. by practical actions and win in the confrontation with the U.S. by definitely achieving national cooperation under the banner of the Korean nation-first spirit.

Japanese Authorities Urged to Improve Relations with DPRK 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 3 (KCNA) -- A meeting was held by political parties and public organizations of Bangladesh in Dhaka on Feb. 25 to condemn Japan's adoption of the "amendment to the law on foreign exchange".
 It was attended by Rashed Khan Menon, chairman of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party, Khaalequzzaman Bhuiyan, chairman of the Central Committee of the Socialist Party, Mujahidul Islam Selim, general secretary of Central Committee of the Communist Party, A.F.M. Mahbubl Huq, governor of the Central Committee of the Socialist Party, Dilip Barua, general secretary of the Central Committee of the Communist Party (Marxist-Leninist), and other leaders of political parties and their members, members of organizations for friendship and solidarity with the Korean people and people from all walks of life. 
 Nuran Nabie, general secretary of the Bangladesh-Korea Friendship Association, and other personages in their speeches charged that Japan's "amendment to the law on foreign exchange" is aimed at suffocating, isolating and stifling the DPRK economically. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They stressed that the progressive political parties and people of Bangladesh would positively support all the countermeasures taken by the DPRK against Japan's moves against it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They strongly demanded the Japanese authorities lift the sanctions against the DPRK, though belatedly, with the reasonable way of thinking and fully apologize and compensate the Korean people for the unspeakable damage and sufferings Japan brought to them during its colonial rule over Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A letter of protest to the chief executive of Japan was adopted at the meeting. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It stressed that Japan's adoption of the "amendment to the law on foreign exchange" diametrically runs counter to the DPRK-Japan Pyongyang Declaration in which both promised to observe international law and refrain from threatening each other's security. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It urged the Japanese authorities to stop their anti-DPRK moves and opt for improving the relations with the DPRK.

New Organization Formed in S. Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 3 (KCNA) -- The "Headquarters of the Movement for National Assembly Election to Judge Outdated Politics in the June 15 Era" was reportedly formed in south Korea on Feb. 27.
 The headquarters is formed of the Reunification Solidarity, the National Alliance for Democracy and Reunification, the South Headquarters of the National Alliance for the Country's Reunification, the National Federation of Peasants Associations, the Solidarity for Implementing the South-North Joint Declaration, the South Korean Federation of University Student Councils and other organizations of the movement for democracy and reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The main target of its activity is to achieve independence and reunification in the June 15 era and force the "Grand National Party" out of the political scene. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The inaugural ceremony of the organization was held in Anguk-Dong, Seoul, that day. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The speakers, elaborating on the purport of the formation of the organization, said now the people hope for the total dissolution of the GNP, the conservative and corrupt anti-reunification party, and the appearance of a new political force in the June 15 era. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Therefore, they stated, we are forming this organization to create a new political environment in the June 15 era and to remove the GNP and bring an epochal turn in the course of independent and peaceful reunification jointly with all the people standing behind the joint declaration in the forthcoming national assembly election. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The declaration published at the inaugural meeting said the headquarters would make efforts to give birth to the 17th "National Assembly" which would promote the peaceful reunification and democratic reforms by waging a movement for dissolving the GNP and voting down corrupt politicians. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It was stated at the inaugural ceremony that the headquarters would start multi-concurrently "an inaugural ceremony for the judgment of antiquated politics in the June 15 era under the Headquarters of the Movement for the National Assembly Election," the "movement for the removal of the GNP" along with a campaign demanding "National Assembly" endorsement of the implementation of the joint declaration and removal of the "security law" in all parts of south Korea in days ahead.

Japan's Hostile Policy towards DPRK Condemned 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 3 (KCNA) -- A spokesman for the Committee for the Peaceful Reunification of the Fatherland issued a statement on March 2 on the occasion of the 85th anniversary of the historic March 1 Popular Uprising.
 The uprising was a nation-wide resistance against Japan as it fully demonstrated to the world the indomitable stamina and patriotic fighting spirit of the Korean people in their struggle to regain the dignity of the nation and sovereignty and independence of the country and dealt a heavy blow at the Japanese imperialists' colonial rule, the statement noted, and continued: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Nearly 60 years have passed since Korea was liberated from the colonial rule of the Japanese imperialists. But Japan has not repented of the hideous crimes it committed in the past but is acting a shock brigade in executing the U.S. measures to stifle the DPRK, pursuant to its hostile policy toward the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Recently the Japanese reactionaries passed through the Diet "an amendment to the law on foreign exchange" aimed at applying sanctions against the DPRK and stifling it and are working hard to adopt a "bill banning portcalls of specified foreign ships." This is an unpardonable criminal act adding to their crimes. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They are persistently pursuing the hostile policy towards the DPRK to implement the U.S. policy to stifle the DPRK. But they should bear in mind they will get nothing by doing so. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 If Japan, oblivious of its bitter past, sets out again on overseas aggression, toeing the US line, it will bring such fatal consequences as the disappearance of Japan, a country of islands, from this earth. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japanese reactionaries had better properly understand the will of the Korean nation to force Japan to redeem its crimes committed against the Koreans generation after generation and stop acting rashly. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We earnestly call on the south Korean people from all walks of life to dynamically rise up in the sacred anti-U.S. and anti-Japanese resistance to decisively smash the moves of the U.S. and Japanese aggressors for domination, interference, aggression and war through national cooperation in order to defend the peace of the country and bring earlier the day of independent reunification of the nation.

U.S. President's Proposal under Fire 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 3 (KCNA) -- U.S. President Bush made a "proposal for non-proliferation of weapons of mass destruction (WMD)" in a recent speech at National Defense University in Washington.
 Rodong Sinmun today in a signed commentary dismisses this as a sheer fallacy intended to reinforce the U.S.-led "Proliferation Security Initiative (PSI)" in a bid to paralyze the function of the present international legal system and realize its ambition for world supremacy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Bush's proposal is aimed to legalize the U.S.-led "marine and aerial blockade system" for the expansion and strengthening of the"PSI" publicized in 2003 and establish such a brigandish system for interfering in internal affairs of other countries as one for "punishing" independent non-nuclear states through the expansion of the sphere of its application. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The proposal is an unequal proposal based on double standards quite contrary to the UN Charter calling for equality of all countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 What should not be overlooked is that the proposal is intended to isolate and stifle the DPRK. The U.S. "PSI" is a measure to isolate and blockade the DPRK in the light of its origin and purpose. The U.S. is working hard to force other countries to follow its hostile policy toward the DPRK, not content with labeling the DPRK's increase of its military power for self-defense as a proliferation of WMD and even banning the export of goods for dual use. The U.S. is sadly mistaken if it thinks it can browbeat the DPRK through the "PSI ." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 If the U.S. sincerely wants the "non-proliferation of WMD" and the peaceful settlement of the nuclear issue on the Korean peninsula, it should admit its responsibility for having proliferated WMD worldwide and take practical actions to drop its hostile policy to stifle the DPRK, first of all.

CPRF Raps at GNP's Treacheries
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 3 (KCNA) -- The Secretariat of the Committee for the Peaceful Reunification of the Fatherland published information bulletin No. 860 Tuesday.
 Recalling that a "special bill" probing the truth behind pro-Japanese treacheries committed during the Japanese imperialists' colonial rule over Korea was scheduled to be laid before a plenary session of the "National Assembly" of south Korea on Feb. 27 but it ended abortive owing to the opposition of the Grand National Party, the information bulletin says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The GNP's opposition to the deliberation of the "special bill" at the plenary session of the "National Assembly" is an intolerable criminal act of openly trampling upon the anti-Japanese patriotic spirit of the south Korean people and their desire to ferret out to the last man the traitors who sold off the dignity and interests of the country and the nation as stooges of the Japanese imperialists and make them face a stern judgment by history. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The GNP is opposed to the probe into the truth behind pro-Japanese treacheries because it, a group of pro-U.S., pro-Japanese elements and their descendants, would be the first to be brought to justice of history and sternly judged by the nation in case the bill passed through the NA. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The GNP's abuse of the NA as a theatre for trampling underfoot the people's anti-Japanese patriotic spirit fully reveals its true colors as a traitorous political party without an equal in the world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The south Korean people cannot live in peace and the country and the nation cannot get rid of disgrace and disaster with such group of traitors as the GNP left alone. The people from all walks of life in south Korea should build a fiercer flame of the struggle against the GNP they have already started and totally cut off the lifeline of the traitorous party that does so harm but not any good to the country and the nation.
